claim.claim-text:
An apparatus for locating a proper insertion point for a needle, the apparatus comprising:
an elongated body, having a first end region and a second end region, and further comprising an insertion point indication for a needle;
a first reference indicator attached toward the first end region;
a second reference indicator attached toward the second end region; and
markings on the elongated member which indicate proper spacing of the first reference indicator and the second reference indicator with respect to the insertion point.

A method of determining a proper insertion point for a needle, the method comprising:
placing a first reference indicator on or over a clavicle;
placing a second reference indicator on or over a nipple which is on the same lateral side as the clavicle on which the first reference indicator is placed;
sliding an elongated body, which comprises a set of scaled markings on each end of the elongated body and a marked insertion point between the sets of scaled markings, until the first reference indicator and second reference indicator are aligned with equivalent markings on their respective ends of the elongated body.
